But in the symmetric case, we have $C_p = (p/2)^{p/2}$.

So for the general case, we have $C_p = 2^{p/2} \cdot (p/2)^{p/2} = p^{p/2}$.

Therefore, we can state that $\| \sum X_i \|^p \leq p^{p/2} \cdot (\sum \|X_i\|^2)^{p/2}$.

